{
  "scenario": "In H2 2023, right after a hotter-than-expected US CPI print, a major Crypto Exchange announced a merger with a DeFi Protocol that issues a stablecoin. A desk backtest on 1-minute data says: when the exchange’s “merger-arb imbalance” signal triggers, the stablecoin de-pegs (>0.7% off $1) within 24 hours 85% of the time. De-pegs, however, occurred on only 0.4% of days that half-year. The desk proposes using the signal to predict de-pegs.",
