{
  "scenario": "In Q3 2024, following a major policy shift that increased FX volatility, Bank ABC appointed a new head of FX trading. An internal note says ABC’s USD/EM carry book had +2.0% average weekly P&L under the new executive versus +1.0% before, so “the executive change improved returns.” But when split by market regime, in calm weeks returns were +1.5% vs +1.8%, and in volatile weeks -0.2% vs +0.1%.",
