  "explanation": "This is S5 because it provides (i) a clear mechanism: Central Bank buying increases Treasury demand and liquidity, pushing prices up and yields down; and (ii) a dose-response: $10B/day → ~8 bps, $20B/day → ~17 bps, $35B/day → ~31 bps in consistent post-wave windows. The main trap is confusing general risk-off moves during the correction with the incremental, size-dependent effect tied to purchases.",
