  "explanation": "This is S5 because the scenario provides (1) a clear mechanism: the note’s payoff subtracts k times the underlying move, so larger k mechanically amplifies losses when the underlying moves against the holder, and (2) a consistent dose-response: k=0.5, 1.0, 1.5 correspond to -0.2%, -0.4%, -0.6% average daily losses with the same sign each day. The pattern is hard to attribute to confounding since k is the only stated difference and the exposure scaling is contractual.",
