}

{
  "scenario": "In H1 2023, during a sector rotation out of biotech into defensives, Pharma Inc announced a 2-for-1 stock split. A sell-side note claims the split “improved liquidity,” and after controlling for weekly retail-flow intensity, Pharma Inc outperformed a BioTech Start peer basket by 6% over the next month. But the split itself boosted retail-flow in week 1, which influenced whether market makers tightened spreads in week 2 and also affected split-driven momentum into week 4.",
