{
  "scenario": "Over the last 12 months, after an industry disruption and a high-profile renewable developer’s bankruptcy filing, the Treasury launched an “ESG Stabilization Facility” with the Central Bank backstopping purchases of labeled green sovereign bonds. Traders noted that facility-eligible bonds showed 18 bps tighter bid–ask spreads versus non-eligible bonds. However, eligible bonds were moved onto a new Central Bank reporting venue with mandatory real-time quotes, while non-eligible bonds remained largely OTC with delayed, end-of-day composite prints.",
