{
  "scenario": "During high volatility in Q1 2024, TechCorp’s earnings announcement triggered heavy options hedging. RetailGiant’s quant desk “intervened” by routing trades through a new smart-order router (SOR) that tags executions as “earnings-window” and uses microsecond timestamps. Their post-trade model showed TechCorp had 18% lower intraday mispricing versus the Market Index only for SOR-routed flow. But legacy routes aggregate fills to 1-second bins and drop partial fills during halts, inflating measured slippage in non-SOR trades.",
