  "conditionalAnswers": {
    "answer_if_condition_1": "If both SOR and legacy routes used identical timestamp resolution and identical inclusion of partial fills/halts, then YES could be justified because the 18% difference would more likely reflect a real change in execution quality affecting the mispricing metric.",
    "answer_if_condition_2": "If the SOR’s improved logging is the only difference (execution venues/strategy unchanged) and legacy continues to miss partial fills in halts, then NO because the observed 18% drop is explainable as a measurement artifact from differential data quality."
