}

{
  "scenario": "In H2 2023, after a surprise CPI print, a Crypto Exchange announced a merger with a DeFi Protocol that issues a stablecoin. The Exchange rolled out a “smart-order routing” toggle to a pilot group. Post-announcement, the pilot group showed 18% lower reported slippage on stablecoin pairs. However, only routed orders were logged with millisecond timestamps and full fill breakdowns; non-routed orders were aggregated into 1-second buckets, missing partial fills and some fees.",
